   "source": [
    "# INTERPRETATION: TOPIC CORRELATION NETWORK\n",
    "#\n",
    "# This network visualizes how topics co-occur across documents.\n",
    "# Edges represent correlations between topic proportions, with thicker\n",
    "# edges indicating stronger associations.\n",
    "#\n",
    "# Community detection reveals clusters of topics that frequently appear\n",
    "# together, suggesting that Responsible AI discourse is structured into\n",
    "# interconnected thematic blocks rather than isolated topics.\n",
    "#\n",
    "# Topics that are closely connected form cohesive areas of discussion,\n",
    "# often reflecting shared conceptual or technical domains (e.g., safety,\n",
    "# evaluation, and risk). In contrast, topics that appear more isolated\n",
    "# may represent distinct or more specialized areas of discourse, such as\n",
    "# governance or stakeholder communication.\n",
    "#\n",
    "# Overall, this structure indicates that Responsible AI discourse is not\n",
    "# uniformly distributed but organized into semi-coherent clusters that\n",
    "# reflect how organizations bundle technical, policy, and social concerns."
   ]
  },
